{
  // The witness leaf (round 1, full pool). The model classifies which statements GENUINELY make
  // this point (cap-2). The provider owns the ask + the prompt rendering (the pool slice is an
  // enumeration of a LIVE set, unrenderable by a static template — and the prompt is the MEASURED
  // p0 form, frozen in providers.js, byte-identical to the imperative reference). It validates the
  // cites on METADATA (in-pool + stance, never a model output) and writes ONLY discrete ids w0/w1 —
  // or the typed miss facts (witnessMiss / noRetrySlice) + the ledger explored/open bookkeeping.
  // Self-flags `Explore` (cast-marker gotcha) — a GENERATED viewpoint arrives with the marker
  // already set (its witnesses came from the generative gate), so this leaf never re-fires on it.
  // Gated on the frame's PoolReady: on a brainstormed (FREE) frame the pool exists only after the
  // Brainstorm leaf ran, and an inadequate pool must never be explored (the imperative early-return).
  "require": ["Viewpoint"],
  "ensure": ["$frame:PoolReady"],
  "provider": ["Dialectic::cite", { "slice": "full", "cap": 2 }]
}
